BRIDGEPORT—Police are shutting down traffic on North Avenue in the vicinity of Lindley Street after a car hit a utility pole around 9:30 a.m., according to police dispatch reports.
No one has been reported injured in the vehicle, which flipped onto its side in the course of the crash, according to fire dispatch reports.
Around two dozen United Illuminating customers were without electricity, according to the utility’s outage website. UI estimates it can restore power around 11:30 a.m.
